benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/customFields - Remove custom fields from invoice item

covered: Valid Deletion: Numerous scenarios confirm successful removal of custom fields under various header combinations and parameters (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC05, TC06, TC11, TC12, TC13).
Non-Existent/Invalid Resources: Tests cover invalid UUID format (TC07) and non-existent invoice item (TC08).
Authorization/Headers: Tests cover missing required header (TC09), and expired/invalid token (TC19) along with header-related regression (TC20).

Error Handling: Various error responses are tested (400 for invalid input or malformed customField param in TC07/TC10/TC15, 404 for not found in TC08, 503 for unavailable service in TC14, 401 for unauthorized in TC19).
Edge Cases: Tests for single field (TC03), no fields (TC04), large field sets (TC12), repeated IDs (TC18), and mixed/invalid IDs (TC17) are included.
Header/Param Robustness: Tests for extra/unexpected query parameters (TC11) and long headers (TC16) address robustness of input parsing.
gaps: Pagination: No explicit tests focusing on API pagination for large result sets or responses when listing/removing many fields across pages.
Caching: No tests asserting caching behavior (ETag/Cache-Control) for DELETE responses.
Rate Limiting: No scenarios verifying behavior under burst or rate-limiting conditions.

Comprehensive Authorization: While TC09 and TC19 cover missing header and token issues, there is no test explicitly for 403 Forbidden or broader authorization failures with valid tokens but insufficient permissions.
Concurrency/Race Conditions: No explicit tests simulating two concurrent deletions or race conditions on the same invoice item.
recommendations: Add pagination-focused tests to validate behavior when removing custom fields across paged datasets, including proper handling of limits and offsets.
Add caching behavior tests to verify ETag/Cache-Control headers on DELETE responses where applicable.
Add rate-limiting/throttle tests to ensure the API gracefully handles bursts of DELETE requests.
Include explicit 403 Forbidden scenarios to cover authorization failures with valid authentication but insufficient permissions, and broaden token/auth scenarios beyond just expired tokens.
Add concurrency/race-condition tests to simulate simultaneous deletions on the same resource to ensure deterministic behavior.
